description.narrative: By 2020 people living in 5 target districts have access to improved water and sanitation services and are practicing safe hygiene behaviours (Target - 15,000 rural people with access to water, 90,000 with access to sanitation and 15 Health Posts with WASH facilities), which contributes to Hygiene, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Wash And Emergencies, Water, Water Supply. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, reduced child mortality and under-nutrition through improved and equitable use of high impact health, nutrition and WASH interventions.

description.narrative: UNICEF WASH support focused on providing a strong enabling environment through commitment by 9 senior policy and decision makers on SDG 6 monitoring and implementation of sanitation policy. Support also centered on participation to strategic global WASH platforms, like SWA, setting the ground for sanitation beyond ODF; and making steady strides towards achievement of ODF targets. 211 aldeias with 102,757 people were triggered, resulting in 55,821 people in 174 aldeias achieving ODF status. UNICEF started the construction of 4 rural water system for hard-to-reach communities. 135 people in these remote areas now have access to basic water supply. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
